    "excerpt": "\r **For archetypal psychology:**\r \r",
    "body": "\r\n**For archetypal psychology:**\r\n\r\n- Carl Jung, *Man and His Symbols*\r\n- Joseph Campbell, *The Hero with a Thousand Faces*\r\n- James Hillman, *Re-Visioning Psychology*\r\n\r\n**For comparative mythology:**\r\n\r\n- Mircea Eliade, *The Sacred and the Profane*\r\n- Karen Armstrong, *A History of God*\r\n- Huston Smith, *The World's Religions*\r\n\r\n**For practical engagement with archetypal forces:**\r\n\r\n- Dion Fortune, *The Mystical Qabalah*\r\n- Starhawk, *The Spiral Dance*\r\n- Georg Feuerstein, *The Deeper Dimension of Yoga*\r\n\r\n**For critical perspectives:**\r\n\r\n- Daniel Dennett, *Breaking the Spell*\r\n- Sam Harris, *Waking Up*\r\n- Remain skeptical while testing frameworks against lived experience\r\n\n---\n\r\n## File: Appendix G Practice The Body as Conscious Instrume 2908a5569f3b800dad0ad8a74444fc5f.md"
